## Problem Context

E-commerce platforms & Retailers face significant inventory inefficiencies due to fragmented decision making across buying, replenishment, store allocation and pricing.

Most inventory decisions are handled independently by different teams using manual spreadsheets, gsheets & biased mental models.

This results in several systemic challenges:

• Excess inventory accumulation
• Frequent stockouts on high-demand SKUs  
• Poor inventory placement across fulfilment centres  
• Slow response to ageing inventory  

These inefficiencies increase working capital requirements, reduce sell-through, directly impacting both topline and bottomline inefficiencies.


## Business Impact

Inventory inefficiencies directly impact several core business metrics:

- Working capital due to high inventory
- Lost revenue due to stockouts on top-selling products
- High logistics costs due to suboptimal inventory placement
- Margin erosion due to excess ageing inventory buildup

Improving inventory decision quality can unlock significant value through better sell-through, increased sales at lower markdowns and reduced operational costs.


