## Product Vision

Build a unified inventory intelligence platform that automates critical inventory decisions across the entire product lifecycle.

The platform should enable:

• Data-driven buying decisions  
• Automated replenishment triggers  
• Optimised store allocations  
• Efficient inventory placement across warehouses  
• Early detection of ageing inventory  

The goal is to move inventory management from manual planning to automated decision systems.


## Product Strategy

The system was designed around modular decision engines that solve specific inventory problems while sharing a common data foundation.

Key strategic principles included:

Decision Automation  
Replace manual spreadsheet-based decisions with algorithmic decision engines.

Unified Data Layer  
Integrate demand signals, inventory data and supply constraints into a single decision platform.

Closed Feedback Loops  
Continuously monitor decision outcomes and refine models using real-world performance.

Scalable System Design  
Ensure the platform can operate across thousands of SKUs and hundreds of retail stores.


## System Architecture

The Inventory Decision Engine operates across five key layers:

1. Data Sources
2. Data Processing
3. Decision Engines
4. Execution Systems
5. Monitoring & Learning

The architecture enables scalable automation of inventory decisions across multiple business functions.


## Core Product Modules

Smart Buying Engine  
Evaluates SKU-level performance signals during intake to prevent non-performing inventory purchases.

Automatic Replenishment Engine  
Continuously monitors demand signals and triggers replenishment decisions.

Store Allocation Engine  
Optimises distribution of inventory across offline stores based on demand patterns.

Inventory Placement Engine  
Optimises warehouse inventory distribution to reduce logistics costs and delivery time.

Ageing Detection Engine  
Identifies slow-moving SKUs early and recommends pricing or liquidation actions.

Pricing Optimisation Engine  
Suggests markdown triggers based on ageing and demand patterns.


## Decision Logic

The system combines multiple inputs to generate recommendations:

Demand Forecast Signals  
SKU-level demand projections.

Inventory Health Metrics  
Sell-through rate, ageing, stock cover.

Supply Constraints  
Vendor lead times, MOQs and fill rates.

Operational Constraints  
Warehouse capacity, logistics costs and store demand.

These inputs feed into decision engines that generate automated inventory actions.


